 [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/article/kaori-icho-pursuing-her-own-perfection\">Feature article</a>[/highlight]\n\nGholamreza Takhti - (Iran) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/gholamreza-takhti\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nHamid Soryan Reihanpour (Iran) [highlight]<a href=\"http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/so/hamid-sourian-1.html\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nSakshi Malik (India) [highlight]<a href=\"https://www.iat.uni-leipzig.de/datenbanken/dbfoeldeak/daten.php?spid=260619AC30654882939E6D98E1CD5B6F\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong>EUROPE</strong></h3>\n&nbsp;\n\nMaider Unda (Spain) [highlight]<a href=\"http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/un/maider-unda-1.html\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nHenri Deglane (France) [highlight]<a href=\"http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/de/henri-deglane-1.html\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nAnna Gomis (France) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/anna-gomis\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nAhmet Ayik (Turkey) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/ahmet-ayik\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nAlexander Karelin (Former USSR - Russia) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/aleksandr-karelin\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nAlexander Medved (Former USSR - Belarus) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/alexander-medved\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nBouvaisar Saitiyev (Russia) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/person/bouvaisa-saitiev\">Profile</a>[/highlight]\n\nDan Kolov (Bulgaria) [highlight]<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Kolov\">Wikipedia</a>[/highlight] [highlight]<a href=\"http://bnr.bg/en/post/100480755/dan-kolov-from-the-village-of-chadarliy-to-world-wrestling-arena\">Feature article (1)</a>[/highlight] [highlight]<a href=\"http://www.novinite.com/articles/115116/Dan+Koloff%3A+Bulgaria\'s+Hero+Who+Perfected+an+Ancient+Greek+Institution\">Feature article (2)</a>[/highlight]\n\nNatalia Vorobieva (Russia) [highlight]<a href=\"https://unitedworldwrestling.org/article/vorobieva-statue-unveiled-in-st-petersburg\">Feature article</a>[/highlight]','Outstanding Wrestlers from around the World','','publish','closed','open','','outstanding-wrestlers-from-around-the-world','','','2018-07-31 17:25:26','2018-07-31 17:25:26','',0,'http://outstanding-wrestlers-from-around-the-world',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(666,2,'2018-07-31 17:25:42','2018-07-31 17:25:42','United World Wrestling (UWW) was founded in 2014 after Nenad Lalovic became President. Wrestling has been present in the modern Olympic Games since in 1896, and the first International Federation for the development of wrestling and weight lifting exists since 1905. After becoming independent as the first International Wrestlers’ Union in 1912, changed its name to Fédération Internationale des Luttes Associées (FILA) in 1953. It was only in 2014 when FILA changed its name to United World Wrestling.\n<h2 id=\"\" class=\"\">United World Wrestling; the organisation</h2>\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1905\" footer=\"\"]\n\nThe first International Federation for the development of wrestling and weight lifting was created in Duisburg, Germany in 1905 by the Deutsche Athleten-Verband (DAV). The goal of the Federation was to set in order the organisation of the World Championships. Years later, the first International Wrestlers’ Union (Internationaler Ring Verband) was created on the eve of the Olympic Games in Stockholm in 1912. The organizing committee of the Olympic Games entrusted the Swedish Athletics Federation with the organization of a congress to draw up the statutes and the rules of an international governing body. The International Wrestlers’ Union became the International Union of Heavy Athletics (Internationaler Amateur Verband für Schwerathletik) and was responsible for the development of wrestling (Greco-roman style), boxing, weightlifting, rope wrestling and weight throw.\n\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1921\" footer=\"\"]\n\nDuring the Antwerp Olympic Games in 1920, the IOC recommended the creation of independent Federations for each sport. The International Amateur Wrestling Federation (IAWF) was thus created during the IOC Olympic Congress in Lausanne in 1921. The statutes of nineteen National Federations and those of IAWF were approved on that occasion, assuming the responsibility of promoting the two wrestling styles and made some corrections to the existing rules.\n\nEinar Raberg (Sweden), was president of IAWF from 1921-24\n\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1924\" footer=\"\"]\n\nAlfred Brull (Hungary), was president of IAWF from 1924-29\n\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1929\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Viktor Smeds (Finland), was president of IAWF from 1929-52</p>\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1952\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Roger Coulon (France), was president of IAWF 1952-54 and FILA from 1954-72</p>\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1954\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">In 1954, the Federation was renamed: International Federation of Amateur Wrestling (FILA, its acronym in French), establishing its headquarters in Lausanne, being the first International Federation to settle in the Olympic capital. FILA introduced new competitions to its calendar (junior World Championships and cadet Continental Championships).</p>\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"1972\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Milan Ercegan (Yugoslavia), was president of FILA from 1972-2002</p>\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"2002\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Raphael Martinetti (Switzerland), was president of FILA from 2002-13</p>\n[/panel]\n\n[panel type=\"info\" heading=\"2014\" footer=\"\"]\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">More recently Nenad Lalovic (Serbia) was elected to serve the remaining two-year term to fill the presidency after the resignation of FILA President Raphael Martintti at a special Congress in Moscow on May 18, 2013. He was re-elected for a full six-year term at the Congress in Tashkent, Uzbekistan, Sept. 7, 2014, where it was approved the name change of “FILA” for UNITED WORLD WRESTLING.\n\nCurrently, United World Wrestling has 179 National Federations affiliated and 1 associate country.</p>\n[/panel]','History of United World Wrestling','','publish','closed','open','','history-of-united-world-wrestling','','','2018-07-31 17:25:42','2018-07-31 17:25:42','',0,'http://history-of-united-world-wrestling',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(667,2,'2018-07-31 17:25:49','2018-07-31 17:25:49','The corporate branding of United World Wrestling represents a holistic concept. The main key symbol of the logo is THE SUN, the central element of the system, provider of energy to the elements around it. Visually, this sun is composed by two wrestlers in its centre, surrounded by flames which symbolizes wrestling fans. The figure is completed by an external circle representing the Combat area of the wrestling mat as a symbol of the wrestling universe.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-814\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/energy-life-light.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"439\" />\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The visual elements of the logo stand for the three values of wrestling as a universal sport: UNITY represented by the sun, INTEGRITY by the wrestlers, and PASSION coming from the fans around the world.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-815\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/visual-elements.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"338\" />\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">As part of their visual identity, United World Wrestling has established related logos to the major wrestling tournaments it runs.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-816\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/brand-tree.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"355\" />','United World Wrestling imagery and values','','publish','closed','open','','united-world-wrestling-imagery-and-values','','','2018-07-31 17:25:49','2018-07-31 17:25:49','',0,'http://united-world-wrestling-imagery-and-values',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(668,2,'2018-07-31 17:25:56','2018-07-31 17:25:56','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">People all around the world, as well as institutions, can get involved in the Sport of Wrestling in any of the following ways:</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Practising wrestling</h3>\n<ul class=\"\">\n 	<li>Wrestlers</li>\n 	<li>Officials</li>\n 	<li>Team staff</li>\n 	<li>Competition staff</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Running the sport</h3>\n<ul class=\"\">\n 	<li>UWW</li>\n 	<li>National Federations</li>\n 	<li>Clubs</li>\n 	<li>Universities</li>\n 	<li>Press and Media</li>\n 	<li>Equipment suppliers</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Supporting wrestling</h3>\n<ul class=\"\">\n 	<li>Fans</li>\n 	<li>Sponsors</li>\n 	<li>Partners</li>\n</ul>','The Wrestling Family','','publish','closed','open','','the-wrestling-family','','','2018-07-31 17:25:56','2018-07-31 17:25:56','',0,'http://the-wrestling-family',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(669,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:01','2018-07-31 17:26:01','<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Summer Olympic Games</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Wrestling was the first Olympic combat sport both of ancient and modern Games, and currently is the combat modality with the highest number of gold medals per edition; one medal set per each one of the 6 Olympic weight categories per wrestling style, total: 18 medal sets for Río 2016. It is also remarkable that wrestling has the highest number of gold medals to be contested by women among Olympic combat sports (6). The qualification process to 2016 Rio Games includes the first 6 wrestlers ranked by each Olympic weight category during the 2015 Senior World Championships, continental Qualifier Tournaments, and three world qualifier tournaments. The following Olympic Games will be Tokyo 2020 and the exact qualification process for 2020 will be announced no later than 2017.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Youth Olympic Games</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Wrestling has been part of the sport program of the Youth Olympic Games since its first summer edition in Singapore 2010. During the second edition in Nanjing, 2014 there was an expanded qualification process that included 177 national federations. A total of 47 nations in 14 weight categories across men’s freestyle, women wrestling and Greco-Roman eventually participated in YOG2014.</p>','Olympic Wrestling','','publish','closed','open','','v-2','','','2018-07-31 17:26:01','2018-07-31 17:26:01','',0,'http://v-2',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(671,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:12','2018-07-31 17:26:12','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Wrestling has a wide presence across the world.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Because of that, it is often included as a fundamental sport in many multisport Games, among others: <b>Continental Games</b> (Panamerican, Asian, African, European Games), <b>Regional Games</b> (i.e. South-American Games, Central American and Caribbean Games, Mediterranean Games), <b>International Multi-Sport Events</b>such as Commonwealth Games, Francophonie Games, Maccabi Games or Military Games, and is also present in the World Universiade (although in this last case not as a permanent sport – that is why United World Wrestling hosts the University Wrestling World Championships every two years).</p>','Wrestling in other multisport events','','publish','closed','open','','wrestling-in-other-multisport-events','','','2018-07-31 17:26:12','2018-07-31 17:26:12','',0,'http://wrestling-in-other-multisport-events',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(672,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:19','2018-07-31 17:26:19','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The international competition system of United World Wrestling is composed by three competition levels, each one with its values and identity derived from the holistic concept of the international federation corporate branding: the competitions as the elements gravitating around the sun.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">World Championships</h3>\n<h5>Prestige, Respect, Performance</h5>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">World championships are the most important International Competitions run by United World Wrestling, convened for age categories over 16 years old in the three Olympic styles. All the 176 affiliated federations around the world may take part. Held annually except the Olympic year for Senior age categories, winners of this tournament are designated WORLD CHAMPIONS.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The correspondent competition logo for World Championships is BLUE, the colour associated with prestige and high performance and symbolising the universe.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-821\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/world-champs-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-822\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/world-champs-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />','Major competitions run by United World Wrestling','','publish','closed','open','','major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling','','','2018-07-31 17:26:19','2018-07-31 17:26:19','',0,'http://major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(673,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:25','2018-07-31 17:26:25','<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Continental Championships</h3>\n<h5>Determination, Pride, Excellence</h5>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Continental Championships are key annual tournaments in each continent with wide participation, where neighboring countries compete in some classic battles. These championships have the same age categories as the World championships. From this level future wrestling stars emerge.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The logo is coloured with BURGUNDY for Continental Championships, a rich and classic colour which represents the excellence of the competition, symbolising the planets among the system.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-824\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/continental-champs-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-825\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/continental-champs-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />','Major competitions run by United World Wrestling (continued)','','publish','closed','open','','major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued','','','2018-07-31 17:26:25','2018-07-31 17:26:25','',0,'http://major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(674,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:32','2018-07-31 17:26:32','<h3>World Cups</h3>\n<h5>Unity, Integrity, Passion</h5>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">With the same values of the United World Wrestling corporate logo, the World Cups are elite annual events with one World Cup per Olympic style for the senior age category only. These competitions consist of an 8 Team tournament format. Qualification is based on:</p>\n\n<ul class=\"\">\n 	<li>The top eight National Federations ranked in the Senior World Championships of the previous year, or</li>\n 	<li>The first seven teams and the host country if the eigth ranked team is not one of the top 8 ranked.</li>\n</ul>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">All the three World Cup logos are GREEN, the color of balance, new energy and growth.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-827\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/world-cups-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-828\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/world-cups-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"585\" height=\"329\" />','Major competitions run by United World Wrestling (continued)','','publish','closed','open','','major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued-2','','','2018-07-31 17:26:32','2018-07-31 17:26:32','',0,'http://major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued-2',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(675,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:37','2018-07-31 17:26:37','<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Golden Grand Prix</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The Golden Grand Prix is the United World Wrestling’s largest prize-earning competition of the annual season, where wrestlers of the three Olympic styles in senior category compete.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Wrestlers qualify to compete in the Golden Grand Prix by earning a medal at the previous world or continental championships, with the specific number of entries based on the qualifying continent. This gives wrestlers the opportunity to earn additional income and giving them the necessary time for which to prepare for the event after the senior world championships.</p>','Major competitions run by United World Wrestling (continued)','','publish','closed','open','','major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued-3','','','2018-07-31 17:26:37','2018-07-31 17:26:37','',0,'http://major-competitions-run-by-united-world-wrestling-continued-3',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(676,2,'2018-07-31 17:26:56','2018-07-31 17:26:56','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">One of the great facts about wrestling is the small cost it requires to get started in the sport. There is very little needed to practice wrestling which means there is very little cost. You have probably already wrestled - wrestling is one of the first things we do as children. When practising the sport it is important to have a safe surface to practice on, one without obstructions where people can get splinters or cut themselves.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">For competitions the <b>wrestling surface</b> is a square or octagonal mat measuring 12 metres on each side. The mat is made of a thick rubber for shock absorption and to provide safety for wrestlers.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-833\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wrestlers-restart.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"451\" />\n[highlight]Two wrestlers re-start the match from the central circle[/highlight]','What do you need?','','publish','closed','open','','what-do-you-need','','','2018-07-31 17:26:56','2018-07-31 17:26:56','',0,'http://what-do-you-need',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(677,2,'2018-07-31 17:27:02','2018-07-31 17:27:02','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The central area, called <b>‘Central Wrestling Area’</b>, is where individuals compete and is a large circle in the middle of the mat which is nine metres in diameter.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Inside this zone, at the middle of the mat, is located a <b>‘central circle’</b> which is one metre in diameter surrounded by a 10cm width band. From here the wrestlers start the match at the beginning of each wrestling period and after any interruption.</p>\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-835\" src=\"http://academy.ftlutte.tn/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wrestling-mat-en.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1201\" height=\"1088\" />\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The outer circle or the combat zone is coloured orange, is 1 meter in diameter and known as the <b>‘passive zone’</b>.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Finally, working from the outside of the mat there is a <b>‘protection area’</b> which is 1.5 metres from the edge of the mat to the outer circle.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Coaches are located on the same side of the mat where the red wrestler is located on the left of the mat and the blue wrestler is located on the right.</p>','The mat','','publish','closed','open','','the-mat','','','2018-07-31 17:27:02','2018-07-31 17:27:02','',0,'http://the-mat',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(678,2,'2018-07-31 17:27:10','2018-07-31 17:27:10','<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Singlet</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The singlet is a one-piece garment made from nylon or lycra which is tight fitting so the opponent cannot grip clothing to use as leverage. The Uniform design must be based on the colours of the flag or team the wrestlers represent, meaning that, during international championships, all countries shall select their uniform by the colours presented in their country’s flag.</p>\nIn addition to the country colours, red or blue markings will remain on the singlets to differentiate the contestants in a single match.\n\n<img id=\"\" class=\"img \" title=\"\" src=\"https://www.unitedworldwrestling.academy/images/courses/97/singlet-flag.JPG\" alt=\"\" />[highlight]Singlets with colors of the Wrestler’ Country flag[/highlight]\n\n<img id=\"\" class=\"img \" title=\"\" src=\"https://www.unitedworldwrestling.academy/images/courses/97/singlets-colours.jpg\" alt=\"\" />[highlight]“Wrestlers during a match with red and blue markings to differentiate the scoring between them”.[highlight]\n<h3></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h5><strong>Shoes</strong></h5>\n<img id=\"\" class=\"img floatleft alignright\" src=\"https://www.unitedworldwrestling.academy/images/courses/97/shoes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"340\" />\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">A special pair of shoes is worn by wrestlers to increase mobility and flexibility. They are light with rubber soles to help give better grip on the mat and usually have protected laces.</p>\n\n<div class=\"request-edit\"></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h5><strong>Headgear</strong></h5>\n<img id=\"\" class=\"img floatright alignright\" src=\"https://www.unitedworldwrestling.academy/images/courses/97/headgear.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"350\" height=\"325\" />\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Headgear is not an essential piece of equipment, but is recommended and is used primarily to protect the wrestler\'s ears.</p>\n\n<div class=\"\"></div>\n<div class=\"request-edit\"></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<div></div>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h5><strong>Handkerchief</strong></h5>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Additionally, to compete in official tournaments, each wrestler should wear a handkerchief, also known as a bloodrag, the wrestler must carry one in their singlet to try and stop any bleeding should this occur or clean up any body fluids from the mat during competition.</p>','Clothing and equipment','','publish','closed','open','','clothing-and-equipment','','','2018-07-31 17:27:10','2018-07-31 17:27:10','',0,'http://clothing-and-equipment',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(679,2,'2018-07-31 17:33:12','2018-07-31 17:33:12','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Wrestling is divided into many different weight divisions in order that athletes are competing against similar sized opponents. This makes it a safe sport and also a sport that is inclusive of all individuals no matter their body type. In order to compete at an optimal weight it is important for wrestlers to not only maintain a good training schedule but to also be conscious of a healthy diet.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Below are a few skills most essential for wrestling:</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Strength</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The ability of the wrestler to exert a force using their muscles. Through strength training this attribute is increased.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Power</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The amount of force produced over a period of time. Power is concerned with how quickly strength can be activated. Therefore, a wrestler could be strong but not powerful if they are slow to move.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Flexibility</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The range of motion (ROM) a body part can undertake. The greater the ROM the greater the flexibility the wrestler has.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Agility</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The skill for a wrestler to change body movements through change in velocity or direction whilst maintaining balance.</p>','Health benefits','','publish','closed','open','','health-benefits','','','2018-07-31 17:33:12','2018-07-31 17:33:12','',0,'http://health-benefits',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(680,2,'2018-07-31 17:33:21','2018-07-31 17:33:21','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">It is a sport not based on brute strength, but to be able to control one’s strength with flexibility, agility, power and speed. By mastering these many physical attributes one builds on their technique but physical skills alone is not enough. Mental toughness is also important where the athlete is prepared to push their body beyond what it normally believes it can do.</p>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">From a young age it is important that future wrestlers develop a good understanding of physical literacy and body control. Wrestlers need to use their neck, back, arms, legs and body in order to be successful and through the development of good body control a wrestler will become more confident in their ability to execute wrestling moves effectively and efficiently. Wrestlers also should be able to get a safe relationship with the surface of the mat, which means landing safely in different situations, rolling over and being able to change positions quickly. Flexibility is also important and therefore improving joint range of motion during specific techniques or tasks will help reduce the risk of injury.</p>','Controlling your body','','publish','closed','open','','controlling-your-body','','','2018-07-31 17:33:21','2018-07-31 17:33:21','',0,'http://controlling-your-body',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(681,2,'2018-07-31 17:33:29','2018-07-31 17:33:29','<p id=\"\" class=\"\">There are many values associated with wrestling and although it is an individual sport is creates great camaraderie through team achievement. There are many attributes that are developed through being a wrestler other than the physical attributes mentioned earlier. Some of these areas of personal development include:</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Personal responsibility</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">As an individual sport it is up to the wrestler to ensure that they maintain training, making weight and scoring in bouts. In team tournaments this responsibility contributes to the whole where they have a commitment to one another.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Camaraderie</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">As a member of a wrestling team athletes compete against each other day in day out with practice and develop a great amount of empathy with wins and losses in tournaments. This bond develops lifelong friendships and life skills which are drawn on far beyond the walls of wrestling training halls. Through training individuals also develop other important life skills such as punctuality.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Discipline</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">To be successful in wrestling the athlete must have discipline to maintain a dedicated training routine to continually develop technique, strength, power, agility and also maintain weight in the long term.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Focus</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">The very best wrestlers usually have one or two moves of mastery. This is gained through years of practice and repetition where they focused on mastering these moves rather than doing many things less often.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"\" class=\"\">Fun</h3>\n<p id=\"\" class=\"\">Overall the sport is fun!</p>','Wrestling and personal development','','publish','closed','open','','wrestling-and-personal-development','','','2018-07-31 17:33:29','2018-07-31 17:33:29','',0,'http://wrestling-and-personal-development',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1024,2,'2018-08-02 17:19:33','2018-08-02 17:19:33','[qsm quiz=4]','How to wrestle [QUIZ]','','publish','closed','closed','','how-to-wrestle-quiz','','','2018-08-02 17:19:33','2018-08-02 17:19:33','',0,'http://how-to-wrestle-quiz',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1027,2,'2018-08-02 17:39:32','2018-08-02 17:39:32','[qsm quiz=5]','The history of Wrestling [QUIZ]','','publish','closed','closed','','the-history-of-wrestling-quiz','','','2018-08-02 17:39:32','2018-08-02 17:39:32','',0,'http://the-history-of-wrestling-quiz',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1031,2,'2018-08-02 17:57:07','2018-08-02 17:57:07','[qsm quiz=6]','United World Wrestlin