ting control allows to use a tactical procedure to obtain a wanted opportunity.\r\n\r\nGenerally a grip series, it can also be a single grip, no contact, or even the hold of the opponent.​','P1 / STARTING PHASE','','publish','closed','closed','','p1-starting-phase','','','2018-11-23 12:03:44','2018-11-23 12:03:44','',0,'http://p1-starting-phase',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1418,1,'2018-11-23 11:14:29','2018-11-23 11:14:29','<strong>STANCES:</strong> We will distinguish the standing stances from the ground stances. Among the standing stances, we commonly observe two stance distances: mid-distance stance and in contact stance. There are three stance levels: the low, the medium and the high. These levels fit to a personal style or a specific wrestling school. The nature of the stance can lead to offensive (shifted stance) or defensive (aligned stance) attitudes.​\r\n\r\nThe front to front stance and the front to back stance are the two main ground stances. The four-point position of the defender is more offensive, the flat par terre position is more defensive.​','P1 / STARTING PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1417-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:14:29','2018-11-23 11:14:29','',1417,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1417-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1419,1,'2018-11-23 11:14:58','2018-11-23 11:14:58','<strong>STANCES:</strong> We will distinguish the standing stances from the ground stances.\r\n\r\nAmong the standing stances, we commonly observe two stance distances: mid-distance stance and in contact stance.\r\n\r\nThere are three stance levels: the low, the medium and the high.\r\n\r\nThese levels fit to a personal style or a specific wrestling school.\r\n\r\nThe nature of the stance can lead to offensive (shifted stance) or defensive (aligned stance) attitudes.​\r\n\r\nThe front to front stance and the front to back stance are the two main ground stances. The four-point position of the defender is more offensive, the flat par terre position is more defensive.​','P1 / STARTING PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1417-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:14:58','2018-11-23 11:14:58','',1417,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1417-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1420,1,'2018-11-23 11:15:48','2018-11-23 11:15:48','<strong>STANCES:</strong> We will distinguish the standing stances from the ground stances.\r\n\r\nAmong the standing stances, we commonly observe two stance distances: mid-distance stance and in contact stance.\r\n\r\nThere are three stance levels: the low, the medium and the high.\r\n\r\nThese levels fit to a personal style or a specific wrestling school.\r\n\r\nThe nature of the stance can lead to offensive (shifted stance) or defensive (aligned stance) attitudes.​\r\n\r\nThe front to front stance and the front to back stance are the two main ground stances. The four-point position of the defender is more offensive, the flat par terre position is more defensive.​\r\n\r\n<strong>STANCE-STARTING CONTROL LINK:</strong> This link is a technical/tactical operation to reach a starting control.\r\n\r\nIt integrates a tactical component (information processing, decision-making, anticipation, timing) and a technical component (release of arms, distance and displacement quality).\r\n\r\nWe will find this link for the leg attacks and nearly all starting controls in the in contact wrestling.​','P1 / STARTING PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1417-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:15:48','2018-11-23 11:15:48','',1417,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1417-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1421,1,'2018-11-23 11:16:23','2018-11-23 11:16:23','<strong>STANCES:</strong> We will distinguish the standing stances from the ground stances.\r\n\r\nAmong the standing stances, we commonly observe two stance distances: mid-distance stance and in contact stance.\r\n\r\nThere are three stance levels: the low, the medium and the high.\r\n\r\nThese levels fit to a personal style or a specific wrestling school.\r\n\r\nThe nature of the stance can lead to