se',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1423,1,'2018-11-23 11:16:55','2018-11-23 11:16:55','The technical/tactical combination is an invariable sequence of three phases:\r\n\r\n[list icon=\"check\" color=\"accent, dark\"]\r\n\r\n[li]<span class=\"TextRun SCXP52879571\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXP52879571\">a starting phase</span></span>[/li]\r\n\r\n[li]<span class=\"TextRun SCXP52879571\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXP52879571\">a preparation phase</span></span>[/li]\r\n\r\n[li]<span class=\"TextRun SCXP52879571\" lang=\"EN-GB\" xml:lang=\"EN-GB\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXP52879571\">a technical phase</span></span>[/li]\r\n\r\n[/list]\r\n\r\nThe wrestling technique is contextualized be the use of a tactical process from a given starting control.​\r\n\r\nThese phases are linked one another and are composed of different elements according to the combinations:\r\n\r\n<strong>P1 / Starting phase:​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Stance​</li>\r\n 	<li>Stance-starting control link​</li>\r\n 	<li>Starting control</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;335562766&quot;:4,&quot;335562767&quot;:0,&quot;335562768&quot;:4,&quot;335562769&quot;:0}\"><b>P2 / Preparation </b><b>phase:</b>​</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n 	<li data-charcodes=\"8226\" data-font=\"Arial,Sans-Serif\" data-buautonum=\"8\" data-margin=\"450\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Pre-action​</li>\r\n 	<li data-charcodes=\"8226\" data-font=\"Arial,Sans-Serif\" data-buautonum=\"8\" data-margin=\"450\" data-aria-posinset=\"2\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Opportunity</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1,&quot;335559683&quot;:0,&quot;335559685&quot;:0,&quot;335559731&quot;:0,&quot;335559737&quot;:0,&quot;335562764&quot;:2,&quot;335562765&quot;:1,&quot;335562766&quot;:4,&quot;335562767&quot;:0,&quot;335562768&quot;:4,&quot;335562769&quot;:0}\"><b>P3 / Technical </b><b>phase:</b>​</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"font-weight: 400;\">\r\n 	<li data-charcodes=\"8226\" data-font=\"Arial,Sans-Serif\" data-buautonum=\"8\" data-margin=\"450\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Sequence of holds​</li>\r\n 	<li data-charcodes=\"8226\" data-font=\"Arial,Sans-Serif\" data-buautonum=\"8\" data-margin=\"450\" data-aria-posinset=\"2\" data-aria-level=\"1\"><b>Technique</b>​</li>\r\n 	<li data-charcodes=\"8226\" data-font=\"Arial,Sans-Serif\" data-buautonum=\"8\" data-margin=\"450\" data-aria-posinset=\"3\" data-aria-level=\"1\">Finish</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDuring the match itself, this series can be more complex. Indeed, the wrestlers will be able to ​continue the combination after the block or evasion of their opponent.​','THE TECHNICAL/TACTICAL COMBINATION','','inherit','closed','closed','','1412-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:16:55','2018-11-23 11:16:55','',1412,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1412-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1424,1,'2018-11-23 11:18:31','2018-11-23 11:18:31','<strong>PRE-ACTION:</strong> The pre-action is the tactical procedure which creates an opportunity to realize a wrestling technique:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>a fake attack,</li>\r\n 	<li>a bait,</li>\r\n 	<li>a constraining hold,</li>\r\n 	<li>a position,</li>\r\n 	<li>a displacement, etc.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>OPPORTUNITY:</strong> The opportunity is the right chance to execute a wrestling technique, the moment to engage the technique.\r\n\r\nIt is necessary to know the opportunity related to the execution of a technique to plan to create it.​','P2 / PREPARATION PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1422-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:18:31','2018-11-23 11:18:31','',1422,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1422-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1425,2,'2018-11-23 11:18:46','2018-11-23 11:18:46','<strong>SEQUENCE OF HOLDS:</strong> To use the opportunity, the execution of the technique often requires a link between the starting control and the execution hold.\r\n\r\nTaking advantage of an opening or a loss of balance, this link must be quickly executed before the opponent regains his or her stability.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EXECUTION HOLD:</strong> The execution hold is a grip series that allows the execution of a wrestling technique.\r\n\r\nIt can be either the same as starting control or different.\r\n\r\nVariations are possible for each execution hold.​\r\n\r\n<strong>WRESTLING TECHNIQUE:</strong> The wrestling technique is the association of an execution hold and a body movement (overthrow or turn-over).​\r\n\r\n<strong>FINISH:</strong> It is the final phase of the technical/tactical combination.\r\n\r\nLinked to the wrestling technique, it results in maintenance of the opponent into danger position or back control position.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SEQUENCE OF MOVES:</strong> After the execution of a first combination, the attacker finds himself or herself with a new starting control.\r\n\r\nHe or she continues the action with a new combination without downtime position.​','P3 / TECHNICAL PHASE','','publish','closed','closed','','p3-technical-phase','','','2018-11-23 12:04:00','2018-11-23 12:04:00','',0,'http://p3-technical-phase',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1426,1,'2018-11-23 11:20:45','2018-11-23 11:20:45','<strong>SEQUENCE OF HOLDS:</strong> To use the opportunity, the execution of the technique often requires a link between the starting control and the execution hold.\r\n\r\nTaking advantage of an opening or a loss of balance, this link must be quickly executed before the opponent regains his or her stability.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EXECUTION HOLD:</strong> The execution hold is a grip series that allows the execution of a wrestling technique.\r\n\r\nIt can be either the same as starting control or different.\r\n\r\nVariations are possible for each execution hold.​\r\n\r\n<strong>WRESTLING TECHNIQUE:</strong> The wrestling technique is the association of an execution hold and a body movement (overthrow or turn-over).​\r\n\r\n<strong>FINISH:</strong> It is the final phase of the technical/tactical combination.\r\n\r\nLinked to the wrestling technique, it results in maintenance of the opponent into danger position or back control position.​\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','P3 / TECHNICAL PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1425-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:20:45','2018-11-23 11:20:45','',1425,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1425-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1427,1,'2018-11-23 11:21:11','2018-11-23 11:21:11','<strong>SEQUENCE OF HOLDS:</strong> To use the opportunity, the execution of the technique often requires a link between the starting control and the execution hold.\r\n\r\nTaking advantage of an opening or a loss of balance, this link must be quickly executed before the opponent regains his or her stability.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EXECUTION HOLD:</strong> The execution hold is a grip series that allows the execution of a wrestling technique.\r\n\r\nIt can be either the same as starting control or different.\r\n\r\nVariations are possible for each execution hold.​\r\n\r\n<strong>WRESTLING TECHNIQUE:</strong> The wrestling technique is the association of an execution hold and a body movement (overthrow or turn-over).​\r\n\r\n<strong>FINISH:</strong> It is the final phase of the technical/tactical combination.\r\n\r\nLinked to the wrestling technique, it results in maintenance of the opponent into danger position or back control position.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SEQUENCE OF MOVES:</strong> After the execution of a first combination, the attacker finds himself or herself with a new starting control.\r\n\r\nHe or she continues the action with a new combination without downtime position.​','P3 / TECHNICAL PHASE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1425-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:21:11','2018-11-23 11:21:11','',1425,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1425-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1428,2,'2018-11-23 11:23:06','2018-11-23 11:23:06','The technical/tactical complex is a combination of series (we also speak of radiation or systematic combination) from a same starting control. We will distinguish several categories of technical/tactical complexes according to the attacks.​\r\n\r\n<strong>For standing positions, we will distinguish:​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Mid-stance direct attacks​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Leg attacks​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from inside or under control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks and counter-attacks from outside or over control​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For par terre positions, we will distinguish:​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks and counter-attacks from front control or under​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from head and arm control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from body lock or leg on leg control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from arm control on legs</strong></li>\r\n</ul>','THE TECHNICAL/TACTICAL COMPLEX','','publish','closed','closed','','the-technical-tactical-complex','','','2018-11-23 12:04:23','2018-11-23 12:04:23','',0,'http://the-technical-tactical-complex',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1429,1,'2018-11-23 11:26:00','2018-11-23 11:26:00','The technical/tactical complex is a combination of series (we also speak of radiation or systematic combination) from a same starting control. We will distinguish several categories of technical/tactical complexes according to the attacks.​\r\n\r\n<strong>For standing positions, we will distinguish:​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Mid-stance direct attacks​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Leg attacks​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from inside or under control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks and counter-attacks from outside or over control​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>For par terre positions, we will distinguish:​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks and counter-attacks from front control or under​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from head and arm control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from body lock or leg on leg control​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Attacks from arm control on legs</strong></li>\r\n</ul>','THE TECHNICAL/TACTICAL COMPLEX','','inherit','closed','closed','','1428-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:26:00','2018-11-23 11:26:00','',1428,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1428-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1430,2,'2018-11-23 11:26:30','2018-11-23 11:26:30','<strong>BLOCK:</strong> The block is a defensive action (movement, freeing, etc.) done during a wrestling technique to stop it from happening.\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EVASION:</strong> The evasion is the freeing action which allows avoiding the attack or the opponent’s hold access (starting control or execution hold).\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER-ATTACK:</strong> A counter-attack is a technical/tactical combination starting from the opponent’s attack or executed by the wrestler dominated on the ground (back control of the opponent).​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER:</strong> The counter is a move which blocks the opponent during his or her attacks and gives the blocker an advantage position.​','DEFENCE','','publish','closed','closed','','defence','','','2018-11-23 12:04:29','2018-11-23 12:04:29','',0,'http://defence',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1431,2,'2018-11-23 11:27:16','2018-11-23 11:27:16','<strong>BLOCK:</strong> The block is a defensive action (movement, freeing, etc.) done during a wrestling technique to stop it from happening.\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EVASION:</strong> The evasion is the freeing action which allows avoiding the attack or the opponent’s hold access (starting control or execution hold).\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER-ATTACK:</strong> A counter-attack is a technical/tactical combination starting from the opponent’s attack or executed by the wrestler dominated on the ground (back control of the opponent).​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER:</strong> The counter is a move which blocks the opponent during his or her attacks and gives the blocker an advantage position.​','SHIFTS​','','publish','closed','closed','','defence-2','','','2018-11-23 11:36:42','2018-11-23 11:36:42','',0,'http://defence-2',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1432,1,'2018-11-23 11:28:36','2018-11-23 11:28:36','<strong>BLOCK:</strong> The block is a defensive action (movement, freeing, etc.) done during a wrestling technique to stop it from happening.\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EVASION:</strong> The evasion is the freeing action which allows avoiding the attack or the opponent’s hold access (starting control or execution hold).\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER-ATTACK:</strong> A counter-attack is a technical/tactical combination starting from the opponent’s attack or executed by the wrestler dominated on the ground (back control of the opponent).​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER:</strong> The counter is a move which blocks the opponent during his or her attacks and gives the blocker an advantage position.​','DEFENCE','','inherit','closed','closed','','1431-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:28:36','2018-11-23 11:28:36','',1431,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1431-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1433,2,'2018-11-23 11:30:32','2018-11-23 11:30:32','The wrestling actions executed to overthrow or turn over an opponent make use of a system of forces which act around a centre of axis of rotation.\r\n\r\nSeveral fundamental wrestling moves can be characterized by the system of forces used (nature, direction, and ways of used forces) and by centre of axis of rotation around which the unbalance will be produced.\r\n\r\nThe specified direction is always the principal movement direction executed by the attacker.​\r\n\r\nThese fundamental biomechanical actions are named body movements and can be associated by categories according to their general characteristics.​','BODY MOVEMENTS​','','publish','closed','closed','','body-movements%e2%80%8b','','','2018-11-23 12:04:39','2018-11-23 12:04:39','',0,'http://body-movements%e2%80%8b',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1434,1,'2018-11-23 11:30:54','2018-11-23 11:30:54','The wrestling actions executed to overthrow or turn over an opponent make use of a system of forces which act around a centre of axis of rotation.\r\n\r\nSeveral fundamental wrestling moves can be characterized by the system of forces used (nature, direction, and ways of used forces) and by centre of axis of rotation around which the unbalance will be produced.\r\n\r\nThe specified direction is always the principal movement direction executed by the attacker.​\r\n\r\nThese fundamental biomechanical actions are named body movements and can be associated by categories according to their general characteristics.​','BODY MOVEMENTS​','','inherit','closed','closed','','1433-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:30:54','2018-11-23 11:30:54','',1433,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1433-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1435,2,'2018-11-23 11:31:42','2018-11-23 11:31:42','<h2><strong>A – SHIFTS​</strong></h2>\r\nThe shifts are characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>A downward force using body weight from upper body hold. This creates a planted point.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>A forward, sideways, rotational, backwards, or oriented force to the imbalance direction desired.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is on the ground on one or two of the defender’s feet.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is usually in conjunction with a block or a leg look in freestyle wrestling.​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will distinguish four types of shifts:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift forward​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift sideways​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift in rotation​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Take down</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>SHIFT FORWARD:</strong> A forward attacking action from the hold.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SHIFT SIDEWAYS:</strong> A sideways attacking action in the direction of a line passing through the attacker’s feet or shoulders.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SHIFT IN ROTATION (or with twisting):</strong> A rotational attacking action around the attacker’s longitudinal axis.​\r\n\r\n<strong>TAKE DOWN:</strong> A backwards attacking action obtained by a traction force from the hold. This attacker’s action is in conjunction with a sideways evasion.​','STANDING POSITION BODY MOVEMENTS','','publish','closed','closed','','standing-position-body-movements','','','2018-11-23 12:04:45','2018-11-23 12:04:45','',0,'http://standing-position-body-movements',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1436,1,'2018-11-23 11:32:58','2018-11-23 11:32:58','<h2><strong>A – SHIFTS​</strong></h2>\r\nThe shifts are characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>A downward force using body weight from upper body hold. This creates a planted point.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>A forward, sideways, rotational, backwards, or oriented force to the imbalance direction desired.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is on the ground on one or two of the defender’s feet.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is usually in conjunction with a block or a leg look in freestyle wrestling.​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will distinguish four types of shifts:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift forward​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift sideways​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift in rotation​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Take down</strong></li>\r\n</ul>','STANDING POSITION BODY MOVEMENTS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1435-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:32:58','2018-11-23 11:32:58','',1435,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1435-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1437,1,'2018-11-23 11:35:58','2018-11-23 11:35:58','<h2><strong>A – SHIFTS​</strong></h2>\r\nThe shifts are characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>A downward force using body weight from upper body hold. This creates a planted point.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>A forward, sideways, rotational, backwards, or oriented force to the imbalance direction desired.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is on the ground on one or two of the defender’s feet.​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The planted point is usually in conjunction with a block or a leg look in freestyle wrestling.​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will distinguish four types of shifts:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift forward​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift sideways​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Shift in rotation​</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Take down</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>SHIFT FORWARD:</strong> A forward attacking action from the hold.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SHIFT SIDEWAYS:</strong> A sideways attacking action in the direction of a line passing through the attacker’s feet or shoulders.​\r\n\r\n<strong>SHIFT IN ROTATION (or with twisting):</strong> A rotational attacking action around the attacker’s longitudinal axis.​\r\n\r\n<strong>TAKE DOWN:</strong> A backwards attacking action obtained by a traction force from the hold. This attacker’s action is in conjunction with a sideways evasion.​','STANDING POSITION BODY MOVEMENTS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1435-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:35:58','2018-11-23 11:35:58','',1435,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1435-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1438,2,'2018-11-23 11:36:27','2018-11-23 11:36:27','<h2>B – THROWS​</h2>\r\nThe throws are defined, in a general manner, by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre.​\r\n\r\nWe will distinguish four types of throws:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Body drop​</li>\r\n 	<li>Hip toss​</li>\r\n 	<li>Lift and swing​</li>\r\n 	<li>Suplex​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>BODY DROP / Throw over the shoulder​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upper body control action towards the ground, either forwards or backwards, achieved by placing the attacker’s centre of gravity below the defender’s centre of gravity.​</li>\r\n 	<li>An added upwards action to increase the rotation applied at the back side of the rotational axis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s shoulder.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>HIP TOSS / Throw over the hip​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upwards action obtained by a leg extension and pelvis percussion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A forward downward action achieved by bending the chest in conjunction with the arm action from the upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action by the attacker around his or her longitudinal axis applied from upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s hip.​\r\n<strong>​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>LIFT AND SWING/ Front throw with lift and swing​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An initial upwards action, obtained by either a leg extension, an upward positioning of the back, or the upward action of the upper body hold classically called “a lift”. Once the feet are off the ground, a coupling force&lt; added to or following the lift, will produce a swing moment.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A sideways upward or backwards upward action from the upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A downward forward or sideways action combined with a force (or lever) and the body weight (evasion of a leg).​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is generally the attacker’s chest.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>SUPLEX/ Throw over the belly​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upwards action obtained by a leg extension and pelvis percussion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A backward downward action obtained by dorsal extension applied at the hold level.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotation action by the attacker around his or her longitudinal axis applied from the hold added to a leg evasion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s belly.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n​','THROWS','','publish','closed','closed','','throws','','','2018-11-23 12:05:26','2018-11-23 12:05:26','',0,'http://throws',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1439,1,'2018-11-23 11:36:42','2018-11-23 11:36:42','<strong>BLOCK:</strong> The block is a defensive action (movement, freeing, etc.) done during a wrestling technique to stop it from happening.\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>EVASION:</strong> The evasion is the freeing action which allows avoiding the attack or the opponent’s hold access (starting control or execution hold).\r\n\r\nIt can lead to a counter-attack.​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER-ATTACK:</strong> A counter-attack is a technical/tactical combination starting from the opponent’s attack or executed by the wrestler dominated on the ground (back control of the opponent).​\r\n\r\n<strong>COUNTER:</strong> The counter is a move which blocks the opponent during his or her attacks and gives the blocker an advantage position.​','SHIFTS​','','inherit','closed','closed','','1431-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:36:42','2018-11-23 11:36:42','',1431,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1431-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1440,1,'2018-11-23 11:38:31','2018-11-23 11:38:31','<h2>B – THROWS​</h2>\r\nThe throws are defined, in a general manner, by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre.​\r\n\r\nWe will distinguish four types of throws:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Body drop​</li>\r\n 	<li>Hip toss​</li>\r\n 	<li>Lift and swing​</li>\r\n 	<li>Suplex​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>BODY DROP / Throw over the shoulder​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upper body control action towards the ground, either forwards or backwards, achieved by placing the attacker’s centre of gravity below the defender’s centre of gravity.​</li>\r\n 	<li>An added upwards action to increase the rotation applied at the back side of the rotational axis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s shoulder.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>HIP TOSS / Throw over the hip​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upwards action obtained by a leg extension and pelvis percussion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A forward downward action achieved by bending the chest in conjunction with the arm action from the upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action by the attacker around his or her longitudinal axis applied from upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s hip.​\r\n<strong>​</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>LIFT AND SWING/ Front throw with lift and swing​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An initial upwards action, obtained by either a leg extension, an upward positioning of the back, or the upward action of the upper body hold classically called “a lift”. Once the feet are off the ground, a coupling force&lt; added to or following the lift, will produce a swing moment.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A sideways upward or backwards upward action from the upper body hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A downward forward or sideways action combined with a force (or lever) and the body weight (evasion of a leg).​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is generally the attacker’s chest.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>SUPLEX/ Throw over the belly​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>An upwards action obtained by a leg extension and pelvis percussion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A backward downward action obtained by dorsal extension applied at the hold level.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotation action by the attacker around his or her longitudinal axis applied from the hold added to a leg evasion.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The main axis of rotation is the attacker’s belly.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n​','THROWS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1438-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:38:31','2018-11-23 11:38:31','',1438,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1438-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1441,2,'2018-11-23 11:43:15','2018-11-23 11:43:15','In freestyle and female wrestling, actions on legs will often complement the attack. The nature of these actions will be specified:\r\n\r\n<strong>BLOCK:</strong> Leg, foot or arm placed behind, in front of, or beside the opponent’s leg and planting his or her ground support.​\r\n\r\n<strong>HOOK:</strong> Leg placed around the opponent’s foot or leg. It usually favours the opponent’s planted point (like the block) but also allows acting on the hooked segment (in this case it is part of the execution hold).​\r\n\r\n<strong>TRIP, SWEEPING:</strong> A foot trip on the opponent’s foot (sweeping) or a leg trip on the opponent’s leg (trip) to accentuate the torque used around the rotational centre.​','FREESTYLE & FEMALE WRESTLING PARTICULARITIES​','','publish','closed','closed','','freestyle-female-wrestling-particularities%e2%80%8b','','','2018-11-23 12:05:31','2018-11-23 12:05:31','',0,'http://freestyle-female-wrestling-particularities%e2%80%8b',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1442,1,'2018-11-23 11:44:29','2018-11-23 11:44:29','In freestyle and female wrestling, actions on legs will often complement the attack. The nature of these actions will be specified:\r\n\r\n<strong>BLOCK:</strong> Leg, foot or arm placed behind, in front of, or beside the opponent’s leg and planting his or her ground support.​\r\n\r\n<strong>HOOK:</strong> Leg placed around the opponent’s foot or leg. It usually favours the opponent’s planted point (like the block) but also allows acting on the hooked segment (in this case it is part of the execution hold).​\r\n\r\n<strong>TRIP, SWEEPING:</strong> A foot trip on the opponent’s foot (sweeping) or a leg trip on the opponent’s leg (trip) to accentuate the torque used around the rotational centre.​','FREESTYLE & FEMALE WRESTLING PARTICULARITIES​','','inherit','closed','closed','','1441-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:44:29','2018-11-23 11:44:29','',1441,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1441-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1443,2,'2018-11-23 11:45:33','2018-11-23 11:45:33','<h2>A – TURNING OVER EXPOSURES ​</h2>\r\nThe turning over exposures are defined by a system of forces applied around a planted point to the ground.​\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>​FORWARD ROLL​</strong>\r\n\r\nThe body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward action from the hold to create a planted point which can be a shoulder, the pelvis, or the shoulder-pelvis axis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A forward action (in front of oneself) from legs transmitted by the chest.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>​TURN​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward fall off or lever action usually using body weight and allowing to create a planted point at the shoulder, pelvis, or knee level.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action moving around a planted point.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nor by​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A pelvis evasion and ground supports inversion, applied downward and allowing creating a planted point at a shoulder, pelvis, or knee level (screwing).​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotation around the longitudinal axis applied at the hold level around a planted support (unscrewing).​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>BACKWARDS TILT​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A fall-off action obtained by the lever action applied from the hold and favoured by the supports placement under the opponent. This action allows to create a planted point which can be a hand, a shoulder, or the pelvis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A backward upward action obtained by leg pushing, dorsal extension and the action applied from the hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action oriented to the opponent and allowing a reversal around a planted support.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>BRIDGING</strong>​\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action (gimlet) applied from the hold, engaged under the opponent with a dorsal extension. This rotation is oriented to the opposite direction of the opponent’s support on the ground which can be the attacker’s head or the opponent’s support (hand, elbow, shoulder, and knee) to the attacker’s feet.​</li>\r\n 	<li>Associated with the attacker at the hold level, the opponent turns around the same axis.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>ARCHED​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward action obtained by the use of the body weight and the lever produced by a hook and the dorsal extension. It creates a planted point at the pelvis or shoulder level (hook leg or arm).​</li>\r\n 	<li>An action to the side applied from the hold with a hook and the arms.​</li>\r\n</ul>','PAR TERRE BODY MOVEMENTS','','publish','closed','closed','','par-terre-body-movements','','','2018-11-23 12:05:39','2018-11-23 12:05:39','',0,'http://par-terre-body-movements',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1444,1,'2018-11-23 11:52:07','2018-11-23 11:52:07','<h2>A – TURNING OVER EXPOSURES ​</h2>\r\nThe turning over exposures are defined by a system of forces applied around a planted point to the ground.​\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>​FORWARD ROLL​</strong>\r\n\r\nThe body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward action from the hold to create a planted point which can be a shoulder, the pelvis, or the shoulder-pelvis axis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A forward action (in front of oneself) from legs transmitted by the chest.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>​TURN​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward fall off or lever action usually using body weight and allowing to create a planted point at the shoulder, pelvis, or knee level.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action moving around a planted point.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nor by​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A pelvis evasion and ground supports inversion, applied downward and allowing creating a planted point at a shoulder, pelvis, or knee level (screwing).​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotation around the longitudinal axis applied at the hold level around a planted support (unscrewing).​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>BACKWARDS TILT​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A fall-off action obtained by the lever action applied from the hold and favoured by the supports placement under the opponent. This action allows to create a planted point which can be a hand, a shoulder, or the pelvis.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A backward upward action obtained by leg pushing, dorsal extension and the action applied from the hold.​</li>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action oriented to the opponent and allowing a reversal around a planted support.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>BRIDGING</strong>​\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A rotational action (gimlet) applied from the hold, engaged under the opponent with a dorsal extension. This rotation is oriented to the opposite direction of the opponent’s support on the ground which can be the attacker’s head or the opponent’s support (hand, elbow, shoulder, and knee) to the attacker’s feet.​</li>\r\n 	<li>Associated with the attacker at the hold level, the opponent turns around the same axis.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>ARCHED​</strong>\r\n\r\nThis body movement is characterized by:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A downward action obtained by the use of the body weight and the lever produced by a hook and the dorsal extension. It creates a planted point at the pelvis or shoulder level (hook leg or arm).​</li>\r\n 	<li>An action to the side applied from the hold with a hook and the arms.​</li>\r\n</ul>','PAR TERRE BODY MOVEMENTS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1443-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:52:07','2018-11-23 11:52:07','',1443,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1443-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1445,2,'2018-11-23 11:53:49','2018-11-23 11:53:49','The lifts are characterized by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre or axis:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A first upward action allows taking off the opponent’s support from the ground. It needs anticipation on moves and a quality of supports around the opponent’s centre of gravity.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The reversal is obtained by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LIFT AND TILT​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The lift is here combined to a tilt (cf: standing position body movements):</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LIFT AND SUPLEX​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The lift is here combined to a suplex (cf. standing position body movements)​</li>\r\n</ul>','LIFTS','','publish','closed','closed','','lifts','','','2018-11-23 12:05:44','2018-11-23 12:05:44','',0,'http://lifts',0,'lp_lesson','',0),(1446,1,'2018-11-23 11:59:38','2018-11-23 11:59:38','The lifts are characterized by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre or axis:​\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>A first upward action allows taking off the opponent’s support from the ground. It needs anticipation on moves and a quality of supports around the opponent’s centre of gravity.​</li>\r\n 	<li>The reversal is obtained by a torque applied around an aerial rotating centre.​</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LIFT AND TILT​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The lift is here combined to a tilt (cf: standing position body movements):</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LIFT AND SUPLEX​</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The lift is here combined to a suplex (cf. standing position body movements)​</li>\r\n</ul>','LIFTS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1445-revision-v1','','','2018-11-23 11:59:38','2018-11-23 11:59:38','',1445,'http://192.168.50.4:8081/1445-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1447,2,'2018-11-23 11:59:49','2018-11-23 11:59:49','Some actions cause neither an overthrow nor a turning over of the opponent.\r\n\r\nThey remain however important actions of connection in a wrestling fight.\r\n\r\nThey make it possible to the wrestlers to reach the dominant position of back control and score. ​\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>PASSING BACK:</strong> The passing back is characterized by a fixing of the supports obtained by the action of compressing, drag, push, or level from the hold and a displacement in rotation around this support which allows the attacker to pass behind his or her opponent.​\r\n\r\n<strong>TILT:</strong> The tilt respects the same characteristics. The attacker is under and takes the